{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":3000,"text":"(Video) Announcer: Threats, in the wake of Bin Laden's death, have spiked."},{"time":6000,"text":"Announcer Two: Famine in Somalia. Announcer Three: Police pepper spray."},{"time":8000,"text":"Announcer Four: Vicious cartels. Announcer Five: Caustic cruise lines."},{"time":10000,"text":"Announcer Six: Societal decay. Announcer Seven: 65 dead."},{"time":13000,"text":"Announcer Eight: Tsunami warning. Announcer Nine: Cyberattacks."},{"time":15000,"text":"Multiple Announcers: Drug war. Mass destruction. Tornado."},{"time":17000,"text":"Recession. Default. Doomsday. Egypt. Syria."},{"time":19000,"text":"Crisis. Death. Disaster."},{"time":21000,"text":"Oh, my God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"Peter Diamandis: So those are just a few of the clips"},{"time":26000,"text":"I collected over the last six months --"},{"time":28000,"text":"could have easily been the last six days"},{"time":30000,"text":"or the last six years."},{"time":32000,"text":"The point is that the news media"},{"time":34000,"text":"preferentially feeds us negative stories"},{"time":37000,"text":"because that's what our minds pay attention to."},{"time":40000,"text":"And there's a very good reason for that."},{"time":42000,"text":"Every second of every day,"},{"time":44000,"text":"our senses bring in way too much data"},{"time":46000,"text":"than we can possibly process in our brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"And because nothing is more important to us"},{"time":51000,"text":"than survival,"},{"time":53000,"text":"the first stop of all of that data"},{"time":55000,"text":"is an ancient sliver of the temporal lobe"},{"time":57000,"text":"called the amygdala."},{"time":59000,"text":"Now the amygdala is our early warning detector,"},{"time":62000,"text":"our danger detector."},{"time":64000,"text":"It sorts and scours through all of the information"},{"time":67000,"text":"looking for anything in the environment that might harm us."},{"time":70000,"text":"So given a dozen news stories,"},{"time":72000,"text":"we will preferentially look"},{"time":74000,"text":"at the negative news."},{"time":76000,"text":"And that old newspaper saying,"},{"time":78000,"text":"\"If it bleeds it leads,\""},{"time":80000,"text":"is very true."},{"time":82000,"text":"So given all of our digital devices"},{"time":85000,"text":"that are bringing all the negative news to us"},{"time":87000,"text":"seven days a week, 24 hours a day,"},{"time":90000,"text":"it's no wonder that we're pessimistic."},{"time":92000,"text":"It's no wonder that people think"},{"time":94000,"text":"that the world is getting worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"But perhaps that's not the case."},{"time":101000,"text":"Perhaps instead,"},{"time":103000,"text":"it's the distortions brought to us"},{"time":105000,"text":"of what's really going on."},{"time":108000,"text":"Perhaps the tremendous progress we've made"},{"time":110000,"text":"over the last century"},{"time":112000,"text":"by a series of forces"},{"time":114000,"text":"are, in fact, accelerating to a point"},{"time":117000,"text":"that we have the potential in the next three decades"},{"time":120000,"text":"to create a world of abundance."},{"time":123000,"text":"Now I'm not saying"},{"time":125000,"text":"we don't have our set of problems --"},{"time":127000,"text":"climate crisis, species extinction,"},{"time":129000,"text":"water and energy shortage -- we surely do."},{"time":132000,"text":"And as humans, we are far better"},{"time":134000,"text":"at seeing the problems way in advance,"},{"time":137000,"text":"but ultimately we knock them down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"So let's look"},{"time":143000,"text":"at what this last century has been"},{"time":145000,"text":"to see where we're going."},{"time":147000,"text":"Over the last hundred years,"},{"time":149000,"text":"the average human lifespan has more than doubled,"},{"time":152000,"text":"average per capita income adjusted for inflation"},{"time":155000,"text":"around the world has tripled."},{"time":157000,"text":"Childhood mortality"},{"time":159000,"text":"has come down a factor of 10."},{"time":161000,"text":"Add to that the cost of food, electricity,"},{"time":163000,"text":"transportation, communication"},{"time":165000,"text":"have dropped 10 to 1,000-fold."},{"time":169000,"text":"Steve Pinker has showed us"},{"time":171000,"text":"that, in fact, we're living during the most peaceful time ever"},{"time":174000,"text":"in human history."},{"time":176000,"text":"And Charles Kenny"},{"time":178000,"text":"that global literacy has gone from 25 percent to over 80 percent"},{"time":181000,"text":"in the last 130 years."},{"time":184000,"text":"We truly are living in an extraordinary time."},{"time":188000,"text":"And many people forget this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"And we keep setting our expectations higher and higher."},{"time":193000,"text":"In fact, we redefine what poverty means."},{"time":196000,"text":"Think of this, in America today,"},{"time":198000,"text":"the majority of people under the poverty line"},{"time":201000,"text":"still have electricity, water, toilets, refrigerators,"},{"time":204000,"text":"television, mobile phones,"},{"time":206000,"text":"air conditioning and cars."},{"time":209000,"text":"The wealthiest robber barons of the last century, the emperors on this planet,"},{"time":212000,"text":"could have never dreamed of such luxuries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"Underpinning much of this"},{"time":221000,"text":"is technology,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and of late,"},{"time":225000,"text":"exponentially growing technologies."},{"time":227000,"text":"My good friend Ray Kurzweil"},{"time":229000,"text":"showed that any tool that becomes an information technology"},{"time":232000,"text":"jumps on this curve, on Moore's Law,"},{"time":235000,"text":"and experiences price performance doubling"},{"time":237000,"text":"every 12 to 24 months."},{"time":240000,"text":"That's why the cellphone in your pocket"},{"time":242000,"text":"is literally a million times cheaper and a thousand times faster"},{"time":244000,"text":"than a supercomputer of the '70s."},{"time":246000,"text":"Now look at this curve."},{"time":248000,"text":"This is Moore's Law over the last hundred years."},{"time":250000,"text":"I want you to notice two things from this curve."},{"time":252000,"text":"Number one, how smooth it is --"},{"time":256000,"text":"through good time and bad time, war time and peace time,"},{"time":259000,"text":"recession, depression and boom time."},{"time":262000,"text":"This is the result of faster computers"},{"time":264000,"text":"being used to build faster computers."},{"time":267000,"text":"It doesn't slow for any of our grand challenges."},{"time":271000,"text":"And also, even though it's plotted"},{"time":273000,"text":"on a log curve on the left,"},{"time":275000,"text":"it's curving upwards."},{"time":277000,"text":"The rate at which the technology is getting faster"},{"time":279000,"text":"is itself getting faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"And on this curve, riding on Moore's Law,"},{"time":285000,"text":"are a set of extraordinarily powerful technologies"},{"time":288000,"text":"available to all of us."},{"time":290000,"text":"Cloud computing,"},{"time":292000,"text":"what my friends at Autodesk call infinite computing;"},{"time":294000,"text":"sensors and networks; robotics;"},{"time":297000,"text":"3D printing, which is the ability to democratize and distribute"},{"time":300000,"text":"personalized production around the planet;"},{"time":302000,"text":"synthetic biology;"},{"time":304000,"text":"fuels, vaccines and foods;"},{"time":307000,"text":"digital medicine; nanomaterials; and A.I."},{"time":310000,"text":"I mean, how many of you saw the winning of Jeopardy"},{"time":313000,"text":"by IBM's Watson?"},{"time":315000,"text":"I mean, that was epic."},{"time":318000,"text":"In fact, I scoured the headlines"},{"time":320000,"text":"looking for the best headline in a newspaper I could."},{"time":322000,"text":"And I love this: \"Watson Vanquishes Human Opponents.\""},{"time":327000,"text":"Jeopardy's not an easy game."},{"time":329000,"text":"It's about the nuance of human language."},{"time":332000,"text":"And imagine if you would"},{"time":334000,"text":"A.I.'s like this on the cloud"},{"time":336000,"text":"available to every person with a cellphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"Four years ago here at TED,"},{"time":341000,"text":"Ray Kurzweil and I started a new university"},{"time":343000,"text":"called Singularity University."},{"time":345000,"text":"And we teach our students all of these technologies,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and particularly how they can be used"},{"time":350000,"text":"to solve humanity's grand challenges."},{"time":353000,"text":"And every year we ask them"},{"time":355000,"text":"to start a company or a product or a service"},{"time":358000,"text":"that can affect positively the lives of a billion people"},{"time":361000,"text":"within a decade."},{"time":363000,"text":"Think about that, the fact that, literally, a group of students"},{"time":366000,"text":"can touch the lives of a billion people today."},{"time":369000,"text":"30 years ago that would have sounded ludicrous."},{"time":371000,"text":"Today we can point at dozens of companies"},{"time":374000,"text":"that have done just that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"When I think about creating abundance,"},{"time":382000,"text":"it's not about creating a life of luxury for everybody on this planet;"},{"time":385000,"text":"it's about creating a life of possibility."},{"time":388000,"text":"It is about taking that which was scarce"},{"time":391000,"text":"and making it abundant."},{"time":393000,"text":"You see, scarcity is contextual,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and technology is a resource-liberating force."},{"time":401000,"text":"Let me give you an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"So this is a story of Napoleon III"},{"time":406000,"text":"in the mid-1800s."},{"time":408000,"text":"He's the dude on the left."},{"time":411000,"text":"He invited over to dinner"},{"time":413000,"text":"the king of Siam."},{"time":415000,"text":"All of Napoleon's troops"},{"time":417000,"text":"were fed with silver utensils,"},{"time":420000,"text":"Napoleon himself with gold utensils."},{"time":422000,"text":"But the King of Siam,"},{"time":424000,"text":"he was fed with aluminum utensils."},{"time":426000,"text":"You see, aluminum"},{"time":428000,"text":"was the most valuable metal on the planet,"},{"time":431000,"text":"worth more than gold and platinum."},{"time":434000,"text":"It's the reason that the tip of the Washington Monument"},{"time":437000,"text":"is made of aluminum."},{"time":439000,"text":"You see, even though aluminum"},{"time":441000,"text":"is 8.3 percent of the Earth by mass,"},{"time":444000,"text":"it doesn't come as a pure metal."},{"time":446000,"text":"It's all bound by oxygen and silicates."},{"time":449000,"text":"But then the technology of electrolysis came along"},{"time":452000,"text":"and literally made aluminum so cheap"},{"time":455000,"text":"that we use it with throw-away mentality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"So let's project this analogy going forward."},{"time":462000,"text":"We think about energy scarcity."},{"time":464000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":466000,"text":"we are on a planet"},{"time":468000,"text":"that is bathed with 5,000 times more energy"},{"time":471000,"text":"than we use in a year."},{"time":474000,"text":"16 terawatts of energy hits the Earth's surface"},{"time":476000,"text":"every 88 minutes."},{"time":480000,"text":"It's not about being scarce,"},{"time":482000,"text":"it's about accessibility."},{"time":484000,"text":"And there's good news here."},{"time":486000,"text":"For the first time, this year"},{"time":488000,"text":"the cost of solar-generated electricity"},{"time":491000,"text":"is 50 percent that of diesel-generated electricity in India --"},{"time":495000,"text":"8.8 rupees versus 17 rupees."},{"time":498000,"text":"The cost of solar dropped 50 percent last year."},{"time":500000,"text":"Last month, MIT put out a study"},{"time":502000,"text":"showing that by the end of this decade,"},{"time":504000,"text":"in the sunny parts of the United States,"},{"time":506000,"text":"solar electricity will be six cents a kilowatt hour"},{"time":508000,"text":"compared to 15 cents"},{"time":510000,"text":"as a national average."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"And if we have abundant energy,"},{"time":515000,"text":"we also have abundant water."},{"time":518000,"text":"Now we talk about water wars."},{"time":523000,"text":"Do you remember"},{"time":525000,"text":"when Carl Sagan turned the Voyager spacecraft"},{"time":527000,"text":"back towards the Earth,"},{"time":529000,"text":"in 1990 after it just passed Saturn?"},{"time":531000,"text":"He took a famous photo. What was it called?"},{"time":534000,"text":"\"A Pale Blue Dot.\""},{"time":536000,"text":"Because we live on a water planet."},{"time":539000,"text":"We live on a planet 70 percent covered by water."},{"time":542000,"text":"Yes, 97.5 percent is saltwater,"},{"time":544000,"text":"two percent is ice,"},{"time":546000,"text":"and we fight over a half a percent of the water on this planet,"},{"time":549000,"text":"but here too there is hope."},{"time":551000,"text":"And there is technology coming online,"},{"time":554000,"text":"not 10, 20 years from now,"},{"time":556000,"text":"right now."},{"time":558000,"text":"There's nanotechnology coming on, nanomaterials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"And the conversation I had with Dean Kamen this morning,"},{"time":564000,"text":"one of the great DIY innovators,"},{"time":566000,"text":"I'd like to share with you -- he gave me permission to do so --"},{"time":569000,"text":"his technology called Slingshot"},{"time":571000,"text":"that many of you may have heard of,"},{"time":573000,"text":"it is the size of a small dorm room refrigerator."},{"time":575000,"text":"It's able to generate"},{"time":577000,"text":"a thousand liters of clean drinking water a day"},{"time":579000,"text":"out of any source -- saltwater, polluted water, latrine --"},{"time":582000,"text":"at less than two cents a liter."},{"time":587000,"text":"The chairman of Coca-Cola has just agreed"},{"time":589000,"text":"to do a major test"},{"time":591000,"text":"of hundreds of units of this in the developing world."},{"time":594000,"text":"And if that pans out,"},{"time":596000,"text":"which I have every confidence it will,"},{"time":598000,"text":"Coca-Cola will deploy this globally"},{"time":600000,"text":"to 206 countries"},{"time":602000,"text":"around the planet."},{"time":604000,"text":"This is the kind of innovation, empowered by this technology,"},{"time":607000,"text":"that exists today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"And we've seen this in cellphones."},{"time":613000,"text":"My goodness, we're going to hit 70 percent penetration"},{"time":615000,"text":"of cellphones in the developing world"},{"time":617000,"text":"by the end of 2013."},{"time":619000,"text":"Think about it,"},{"time":621000,"text":"that a Masai warrior on a cellphone in the middle of Kenya"},{"time":624000,"text":"has better mobile comm"},{"time":626000,"text":"than President Reagan did 25 years ago."},{"time":629000,"text":"And if they're on a smartphone on Google,"},{"time":631000,"text":"they've got access to more knowledge and information"},{"time":633000,"text":"than President Clinton did 15 years ago."},{"time":635000,"text":"They're living in a world of information and communication abundance"},{"time":638000,"text":"that no one could have ever predicted."},{"time":642000,"text":"Better than that,"},{"time":644000,"text":"the things that you and I"},{"time":646000,"text":"spent tens and hundreds of thousands of dollars for --"},{"time":648000,"text":"GPS, HD video and still images,"},{"time":651000,"text":"libraries of books and music,"},{"time":654000,"text":"medical diagnostic technology --"},{"time":656000,"text":"are now literally dematerializing and demonetizing"},{"time":659000,"text":"into your cellphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"Probably the best part of it"},{"time":666000,"text":"is what's coming down the pike in health."},{"time":669000,"text":"Last month, I had the pleasure of announcing with Qualcomm Foundation"},{"time":673000,"text":"something called the $10 million Qualcomm Tricorder X Prize."},{"time":677000,"text":"We're challenging teams around the world"},{"time":679000,"text":"to basically combine these technologies"},{"time":681000,"text":"into a mobile device"},{"time":683000,"text":"that you can speak to, because it's got A.I.,"},{"time":685000,"text":"you can cough on it, you can do a finger blood prick."},{"time":688000,"text":"And to win, it needs to be able to diagnose you better"},{"time":690000,"text":"than a team of board-certified doctors."},{"time":694000,"text":"So literally, imagine this device"},{"time":697000,"text":"in the middle of the developing world where there are no doctors,"},{"time":700000,"text":"25 percent of the disease burden"},{"time":702000,"text":"and 1.3 percent of the health care workers."},{"time":705000,"text":"When this device sequences an RNA or DNA virus"},{"time":707000,"text":"that it doesn't recognize,"},{"time":709000,"text":"it calls the CDC"},{"time":711000,"text":"and prevents the pandemic from happening in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"But here, here is the biggest force"},{"time":719000,"text":"for bringing about a world of abundance."},{"time":721000,"text":"I call it the rising billion."},{"time":724000,"text":"So the white lines here are population."},{"time":727000,"text":"We just passed the seven billion mark on Earth."},{"time":730000,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":732000,"text":"the biggest protection against a population explosion"},{"time":734000,"text":"is making the world educated"},{"time":736000,"text":"and healthy."},{"time":739000,"text":"In 2010,"},{"time":741000,"text":"we had just short of two billion people"},{"time":743000,"text":"online, connected."},{"time":745000,"text":"By 2020,"},{"time":747000,"text":"that's going from two billion to five billion"},{"time":749000,"text":"Internet users."},{"time":751000,"text":"Three billion new minds"},{"time":753000,"text":"who have never been heard from before"},{"time":755000,"text":"are connecting to the global conversation."},{"time":759000,"text":"What will these people want?"},{"time":761000,"text":"What will they consume? What will they desire?"},{"time":763000,"text":"And rather than having economic shutdown,"},{"time":765000,"text":"we're about to have the biggest economic injection ever."},{"time":768000,"text":"These people represent"},{"time":770000,"text":"tens of trillions of dollars"},{"time":772000,"text":"injected into the global economy."},{"time":775000,"text":"And they will get healthier"},{"time":777000,"text":"by using the Tricorder,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and they'll become better educated by using the Khan Academy,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and by literally being able to use"},{"time":784000,"text":"3D printing and infinite computing"},{"time":787000,"text":"[become] more productive than ever before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"So what could three billion rising,"},{"time":793000,"text":"healthy, educated, productive members of humanity"},{"time":796000,"text":"bring to us?"},{"time":798000,"text":"How about a set of voices that have never been heard from before."},{"time":801000,"text":"What about giving the oppressed,"},{"time":803000,"text":"wherever they might be,"},{"time":805000,"text":"the voice to be heard and the voice to act"},{"time":807000,"text":"for the first time ever?"},{"time":810000,"text":"What will these three billion people bring?"},{"time":813000,"text":"What about contributions we can't even predict?"},{"time":816000,"text":"The one thing I've learned at the X Prize"},{"time":818000,"text":"is that small teams"},{"time":820000,"text":"driven by their passion with a clear focus"},{"time":823000,"text":"can do extraordinary things,"},{"time":825000,"text":"things that large corporations and governments"},{"time":827000,"text":"could only do in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Let me share and close with a story"},{"time":832000,"text":"that really got me excited."},{"time":835000,"text":"There is a program that some of you might have heard of."},{"time":837000,"text":"It's a game called Foldit."},{"time":839000,"text":"It came out of the University of Washington in Seattle."},{"time":843000,"text":"And this is a game"},{"time":845000,"text":"where individuals can actually take a sequence of amino acids"},{"time":849000,"text":"and figure out how the protein is going to fold."},{"time":853000,"text":"And how it folds dictates its structure and its functionality."},{"time":855000,"text":"And it's very important for research in medicine."},{"time":858000,"text":"And up until now, it's been a supercomputer problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"And this game has been played"},{"time":863000,"text":"by university professors and so forth."},{"time":865000,"text":"And it's literally, hundreds of thousands of people"},{"time":868000,"text":"came online and started playing it."},{"time":870000,"text":"And it showed that, in fact, today,"},{"time":872000,"text":"the human pattern recognition machinery"},{"time":874000,"text":"is better at folding proteins than the best computers."},{"time":877000,"text":"And when these individuals went and looked"},{"time":879000,"text":"at who was the best protein folder in the world,"},{"time":882000,"text":"it wasn't an MIT professor,"},{"time":884000,"text":"it wasn't a CalTech student,"},{"time":886000,"text":"it was a person from England, from Manchester,"},{"time":889000,"text":"a woman who, during the day,"},{"time":893000,"text":"was an executive assistant at a rehab clinic"},{"time":896000,"text":"and, at night, was the world's best protein folder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":903000,"text":"what gives me tremendous confidence"},{"time":905000,"text":"in the future"},{"time":909000,"text":"is the fact that we are now more empowered as individuals"},{"time":913000,"text":"to take on the grand challenges of this planet."},{"time":916000,"text":"We have the tools with this exponential technology."},{"time":919000,"text":"We have the passion of the DIY innovator."},{"time":922000,"text":"We have the capital of the techno-philanthropist."},{"time":925000,"text":"And we have three billion new minds"},{"time":927000,"text":"coming online to work with us"},{"time":929000,"text":"to solve the grand challenges,"},{"time":931000,"text":"to do that which we must do."},{"time":935000,"text":"We are living into extraordinary decades ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}